NAME
       newapi-webhook-poc - Local-only Proof of Concept for New API Stripe 
       webhook forgery vulnerability

SYNOPSIS
       newapi-webhook-poc { --base-url URL | --file FILE }
                           [ --token TOKEN ] [ --trade-no ID ]
                           [ OPTIONS ]...

DESCRIPTION
       newapi-webhook-poc is a security testing utility designed to demon-
       strate a webhook signature verification bypass in PrivHub. The vulnera-
       bility occurs when Stripe is unconfigured (empty StripeWebhookSecret), 
       allowing unauthenticated attackers to forge checkout.session.completed 
       events using a completely empty HMAC secret.

       By default, this tool operates in an automated pipeline. If a known 
       target order (trade_no) is not provided, the tool will attempt to auto-
       matically authenticate, probe the target for applicable payment methods 
       (e.g., Alipay or WeChat Pay), generate a new pending order, and subse-
       quently forge a Stripe webhook to complete that order.

       SECURITY RESTRICTION: As an intentionally constrained Proof of Concept, 
       this tool restricts all outbound network traffic exclusively to loopback 
       interfaces (localhost, 127.0.0.1, ::1). Any attempt to target external 
       network addresses will be safely aborted.

OPTIONS
   Target Specifications
       Exactly one of the following target options must be specified.

       --base-url URL
              Specify a single local base URL to test (e.g., http://127.0.0.1:3000).

       --file FILE
              Path to a newline-separated file containing multiple base URLs. 
              Automatically deduplicates entries and safely skips non-loopback URLs.

       --path PATH
              The webhook endpoint path to append to the base URL.
              Default: /api/stripe/webhook

   Authentication & Order Generation
       --token TOKEN
              Session token to be sent in the HTTP Cookie header (session=TOKEN). 
              REQUIRED if --trade-no is not provided, as it is used to authenticate 
              and auto-create the order.

       --trade-no ID
              A known, pending out_trade_no to inject into the client_reference_id 
              field of the forged payload. If omitted, the tool automatically 
              initiates the order creation routine.

       --topup-amount AMOUNT
              The amount to use when automatically creating a new order.
              Default: 500

   Concurrency & Export
       --concurrency N
              The number of concurrent worker threads to use when processing a 
              target file. 
              Default: 1 (Linear execution)

       --output-json FILE
              Export the execution results, HTTP status codes, and server response 
              details to the specified file in JSON format.

       --output-csv FILE
              Export the execution results to the specified file in CSV format.

   Webhook Payload Parameters
       --customer ID
              Fake Stripe customer ID injected into the event payload.
              Default: cus_poc_local

       --amount-total AMOUNT
              Fake transaction total in Stripe minor units.
              Default: 100

       --currency CURRENCY
              Fake transaction currency.
              Default: usd

       --timestamp UNIX_TIMESTAMP
              Unix timestamp embedded into the forged Stripe-Signature header.
              Default: Current system time

       --event-id ID
              Fake Stripe event ID.
              Default: evt_poc_local

       --session-id ID
              Fake Stripe Checkout Session ID.
              Default: cs_poc_local

       --api-version VERSION
              Stripe API version string injected into the event payload.
              Default: 2020-08-27

   Network Parameters
       --timeout SECONDS
              Maximum time in seconds to wait for HTTP responses.
              Default: 10.0

       --insecure-tls
              Disable TLS certificate verification for targets utilizing 
              self-signed HTTPS certificates.

AUTOMATED WORKFLOW
       When --trade-no is omitted, the tool executes the following sequence:

       1. Probing (GET /api/user/topup/info)
          The tool sends an authenticated request to the topup info endpoint. 
          It strictly verifies that 'enable_stripe_topup' is false. It then 
          scans 'pay_methods' to locate an alternative payment gateway (ei-
          ther 'alipay' or 'wxpay').

       2. Order Creation (POST /api/user/pay)
          Using the discovered payment method and the specified --topup-amount, 
          the tool issues a payment request and extracts the generated 
          'out_trade_no' from the JSON response.

       3. Forgery (POST /api/stripe/webhook)
          The tool crafts a malicious Stripe event payload using the extracted 
          trade number. It signs the payload using an empty string as the HMAC 
          secret and posts it without authentication cookies to bypass the logic.

EXAMPLES
       Target a single local instance with an existing trade number:
              newapi-webhook-poc --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3000 \
                                  --trade-no USR1677NO0rdfFp1776348175

       Auto-create an order and exploit a single local instance:
              newapi-webhook-poc --base-url http://127.0.0.1:3000 \
                                  --token "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIn..." \
                                  --topup-amount 200

       Bulk test multiple local environments concurrently and save to CSV:
              newapi-webhook-poc --file local_targets.txt \
                                  --token "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIn..." \
                                  --concurrency 5 \
                                  --output-csv results.csv

EXIT STATUS
       0      Successful execution of the testing suite (regardless of whether 
              individual targets were vulnerable or rejected the payload).
       1      A critical initialization error occurred, such as invalid arguments 
              or missing dependencies.

AUTHOR
       Written for Security Proof of Concept & Educational Purposes.

LIMITATIONS
       This tool intentionally refuses to operate against external, non-loopback 
       network addresses to prevent misuse. Modifying the LOOPBACK_HOSTS constant 
       voids the safety guarantees of this script.
